LOCATION:GLOBAL &amp\; INTERNATIONAL STUDIES BUILDING - Room Number: 4067
GEO:39.170002;-86.517492
SUMMARY:CANCELED: REEI Colloquium: "Radio Free Europe and Romanian Jazz i
 n Exile" with Grace Pechianu
DESCRIPTION:This talk explores how Radio Free Europe's broadcast 1964 int
 erview and performance featuring defected jazz pianist Eugen Ciceu presen
 ted an alternative\, aggressive paradigm to jazz diplomacy during the Col
 d War. Come learn how Romanian exiles undermined political and cultural i
 solationism while advocating for individual agency and creativity within 
 a democratic\, free market society.  Grace Pechianu is a doctoral candida
 te in musicology at Indiana University\, Bloomington. Her research consid
 ers networks of Romanian exiles and defected musicians\, their role as co
 ntributors to Radio Free Europe\, and role in facilitating communication 
 with Romanians behind the Iron Curtain.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p><span data-olk-copy-source="MessageBody">
 This talk explores how Radio Free Europe's broadcast 1964 interview and p
 erformance featuring defected jazz pianist Eugen Ciceu presented an alter
 native\, aggressive paradigm to jazz diplomacy during the Cold War. Come 
 learn how Romanian exiles undermined political and cultural isolationism 
 while advocating for individual agency and creativity within a democratic
 \, free market society.<br /><br />  Grace Pechianu is a doctoral candida
 te in musicology at Indiana University\, Bloomington. Her research consid
 ers networks of Romanian exiles and defected musicians\, their role as co
 ntributors to Radio Free Europe\, and role in facilitating communication 
 with Romanians behind the Iron Curtain.</span></p>
